<item>
            <title>[JCR-2707] improve performance when saving a node with a large number of child nodes (e.g. &gt; 10k child node entries)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2707</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-307&quot; title=&quot;serious performance degradation of node operations when node has a large number of child nodes (e.g. &amp;gt; 10k child node entries)&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-307&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; brought a significant improvement WRT saving nodes with a large number of child nodes&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
unfortunately &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2579&quot; title=&quot;InvalidItemStateException when attempting concurrent, non conflicting writes&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-2579&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; broke part of the optimization (see NodeState.setChildNodeEntries(List)).</description>
